    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CONFEDERATE FLAG BANNED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen Demasters</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Superintendent of Schools Peter Merluzzi, following bias-related incidents, bans students at New Jersey's Warren Hills Regional High from wearing Confederate flag on clothing (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Students at Warren Hills Regional High School will be prohibited from wearing the Confederate flag on their clothing starting this week, Superintendent of Schools Peter Merluzzi said last week. Several recent bias-related incidents, including distributing racial jokes and waving the flag in hallways, have changed the flag from decoration to a symbol of prejudice, Mr. Merluzzi said. Because of that, he said, the school district attorney has determined the flag can be banned.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
      </block>
